1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
We can see here
a partly overgrown
deep ditch.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Ditches are usually dug
to drain water.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:12,000
But why would anyone
dig them in a forest?

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:16,000
What secret
do they hide?

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,000
These ditches stretch
for many kilometers.

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:24,000
They used to be
even longer.

7
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:28,000
They were dug
from the Oder River

8
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:32,000
near the village of Raków
to Trzebnica.

9
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:36,000
They were part of
a defense line

10
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,000
called “Bartold”.

11
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:44,000
It was meant to protect
Wrocław

12
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:48,000
from the Red Army.

13
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:52,000
These were
anti-tank trenches.

14
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:56,000
They were very deep,
so tanks could not cross.

15
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:00,000
They formed
a continuous line

16
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:04,000
that was hard to bypass.

17
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Only road crossings
were left open.

18
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:12,000
There, concrete blocks
were placed.

19
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:16,000
In case of attack,
they could be blown up

20
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
to block the road completely.

21
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Would this defense line
have worked?

22
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,000
We will never know.

23
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:28,000
The main attack
came from
a different direction.